data.title: You Named it After What Now? Quiz
data.meta_description: Cities are named for individuals, other cities, or often after some interesting feature. Can you match the Canadian provincial capitals with the derivation of their names?
data.text: QuestionsChoices 1. Plenty Edmonton, Alberta 2. Where the river narrows Halifax, Nova Scotia 3. 14th holder of the post of First Lord of Trade Toronto, Ontario 4. Brother of King George IV St John's, Newfoundland and Labrador 5. Muddy water Regina, Saskatchewan 6. First sovereign of the Dominion of Canada Fredericton, New Brunswick 7. First Queen Consort of the United Kingdom Victoria, British Columbia 8. Mother-in-Law of the 4th Governor General of Canada Charlottetown, Prince Edward Island 9. District of North London Winnipeg, Manitoba
